The paper deals with a computer vision problem of co-saliency detection in a single image. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method is an end-to-end trainable network, which involves feature organization and clustering, and uses ground-truth masks as top-down guidance for saliency prediction. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a dataset and experimental results, which indicates that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with visual primitives such as color and shape, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
